######################################################################

This version is for the load phase.

######################################################################

Follow these steps to use the Relational Wide Colomn Store paradigm

Move to root user (or use sudo with following commands)

Install PostgresSQL and other tools for the prog 
    apt-get install make g++ gdb postgresql-12 postgresql-client-12 postgresql-contrib libpq-dev
Configure postgresql
    File location : /etc/postgresql/10/main/postgresql.conf
    See Configs/postgresql.conf
    File location 2 : /etc/postgresql/10/main/pg_hba.conf
    See Configs/pg_hba.conf
    service postgresql restart
VM modifications
    nano /etc/default/grub
        Adapt Configs
        See Configs/grub
    update-grub2
    nano /etc/sysctl.conf
        Adpat config
        See Configs/sysctl.conf
    reboot
Download libpqxx from the repo : https://github.com/jtv/libpqxx
    cd ~
    git clone https://github.com/jtv/libpqxx
    cd libpqxx
    ./configure
    make
    make install
Create environnement variables that will be used for libpq++. Refer to 734 page pg12 documentation
    cd ~
    nano .bash_profile
        export PGHOST=/run/postgresql
        export PGUSER=postgres
        export PGPASSWORD=postgres
    source ~/.bash_profile
    test to log to postgresql with psql command, if logging, installatino ok
If you need to check postgresql configuration, see https://github.com/jfcoz/postgresqltuner


